OL,4,Cthere is 'nothing left to cut'
OL,6,F"But with the cut backs they're not
OL,7,Fgoing to. They'll be denied so many
OL,8,Fprivileges that previous generations
OL,9,Fhave always experienced and expected."
OL,11,FRebecca Phillips, the headteacher at
OL,12,FGlanhowy Primary School, shares many
OL,13,Fof the concerns coming from the
OL,14,Fparents but fears the outlook for the
OL,15,Fschool's finances are unclear.
OL,17,FShe said: "I think we have to be
OL,18,Foptimistic. You have to hope things
OL,19,Fwill get better. I think the reality
OL,20,Fis it's not going to (get better) in
OL,21,Fthe foreseeable future.
